                                            of data thanks to high-standard security protocols (e.g.
                                            no need to send TMs by email)</fo:block></fo:list-item-body></fo:list-item>
                                        <fo:list-item><fo:list-item-label end-indent="label-end()"><fo:block text-align="end"><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman,Liberation Serif,DejaVu Serif,Symbol,Segoe UI Symbol,FreeSerif,ZapfDingbats"></fo:inline></fo:block></fo:list-item-label><fo:list-item-body start-indent="body-start()"><fo:block>Integration with other cloud-based systems (e.g.
                                            Wordpress)</fo:block></fo:list-item-body></fo:list-item>
                                        <fo:list-item><fo:list-item-label end-indent="label-end()"><fo:block text-align="end"><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman,Liberation Serif,DejaVu Serif,Symbol,Segoe UI Symbol,FreeSerif,ZapfDingbats"></fo:inline></fo:block></fo:list-item-label><fo:list-item-body start-indent="body-start()"><fo:block>For bigger
                                            and wealthier enterprises a private cloud is an
                                            option.</fo:block></fo:list-item-body></fo:list-item>
                                    </fo:list-block>
                                    <fo:block-container space-after="0.5em" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="0.5em"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0"><fo:inline font-weight="bold">Biggest threats to using a
