                                        <fo:block-container space-after="0.5em" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="0.5em"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0">Some TMSs
                                            require a filter to be able to process a particular file
                                            format that is either embedded or similar to the native
                                            one. For example, if you want to translate a Markdown
                                            file in memoQ, which is not supported there, you need to
                                            apply a plain text filter. As a result, special Markdown
                                            tags will still appear in the Editor and if used
                                            improperly by a translator, can result in more work to
                                            bring it back to the original format. XTM processes .md
                                            files without a filter so you can save your time and
                                            effort for more productive tasks.</fo:block></fo:block-container>
