                            <fo:block role="Sect" id="unique_19" chfox:nd-id="finance_management">
                                <fo:block-container font-size="1.7em" line-height="1.7em" space-after="0.5em" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="1em" page-break-after="avoid" id="ariaid-title26"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0" role="H2"><fo:inline>Finance management </fo:inline></fo:block></fo:block-container>
                                <fo:block-container space-after="0" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="0"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0">
                                    <fo:block-container font-style="italic" space-after="0.5em" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="0.5em"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0"/></fo:block-container>
                                    <fo:block-container space-after="0.5em" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="0.5em"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0">The main reason
                                        for investing in a TMS is to reduce costs that your
                                        organization spends on translation in general. How can this
                                        tool help you achieve it?</fo:block></fo:block-container>
                                    <fo:block-container space-after="0.5em" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="0.5em"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0">It is best if
                                        you have all the translation costs under control. However,
                                        only a few TMSs have incorporated this important business
                                        management function, XTM being one of them.</fo:block></fo:block-container>
                                    <fo:block-container space-after="0.5em" margin-left="0" margin-right="0" space-before="0.5em"><fo:block end-indent="0" start-indent="0">In the
                                        translation industry pricing strategies are very diverse.
                                        You can be charged per characters, words, lines, both source
                                        and target. It is good practice to agree upon one model with
                                        all of your vendors and apply it in your TMS.</fo:block></fo:block-container>
                                    <fo:block>XTM has two main
                                        features that you can use to manage your translation-related
